SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 157
BY SENATOR PRESSLY
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates Ginger Gustavson for her contributions
and years of leadership in education upon the occasion of her retirement as Head of School
from First Baptist Church School in Shreveport.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate Ginger Gustavson for her contributions and years of
3 leadership in education on the occasion of her retirement as Head of School at First
4 Baptist Church School in Shreveport.
5 WHEREAS, a proud graduate of Benton High School, Ginger Gustavson
6 distinguished herself athletically as an All-State basketball player in 1987 and later
7 competed collegiately in both golf and basketball, and a member of the inaugural LSU
8 Shreveport Lady Pilots basketball team, where she remains among the school's all-time
9 leading scorers; and
10 WHEREAS, in 1993 Ginger graduated from Louisiana State University in Shreveport
11 (LSUS) with a Bachelor of Science in Secondary Math, and in 2008 she earned a Master's
12 Degree in Education plus 30 Graduate Hours from LSUS and went to work in the Caddo
13 Parish school system; and
14 WHEREAS, Ginger's career includes service at Woodlawn High School, Southwood
15 High School, C.E. Byrd High School, Caddo Middle Magnet, Broadmoor Middle Laboratory
16 School, First Baptist Church School, and the Caddo Parish schools central office, during
17 which she served as an administrative assistant for math and physical education at First
18 Baptist Church School and the Caddo Parish school system; a counselor at C.E. Byrd High
