1 School; and a math curriculum specialist in the Caddo Parish school system providing
2 instructional support to math teachers in grades 6 through 12; consistently demonstrating a
3 passion for empowering students and supporting educators; and
4 WHEREAS, Mrs. Gustavson has faithfully served the students of northwest
5 Louisiana in her capacity as a teacher, counselor, curriculum specialist, and administrator,
6 earning the admiration and respect of colleagues, students, parents, alumni, and community
7 leaders by leading with vision, integrity, compassion, and an unwavering commitment to
8 academic excellence and student success; and
9 WHEREAS, under her leadership, Captain Shreve High School experienced
10 continued growth in graduation rates, student achievement, parental involvement, and
11 enrollment, while earning recognition as a National PTA School of Excellence and gaining
12 accolades for student leadership advocacy and academic achievement and she was named
13 the 2020 Louisiana Association of School Executives Regional Principal of the Year, an
14 honor reflecting the profound impact she has made on students, educators, and the broader
15 educational community and in 2021 Ginger was named Caddo Parish Public Schools High
16 School Principal of the Year; and
17 WHEREAS, throughout her career, Ginger has exemplified the value of teamwork,
18 discipline, perseverance, and leadership; the attributes she brought to First Baptist Church
19 School as Head of School beginning in July 2023; and
20 WHEREAS, under her leadership as Head of School, Ginger expanded on First
21 Baptist Church School's history of excellence and was responsible for a major facilities
22 project and the sports complex that will benefit the school's students for years to come; and
23 WHEREAS, Ginger Gustavson has deep roots in education which extend throughout
24 her family, including her parents, both retired educators, her husband David Gustavson, a
25 longtime LSU Shreveport educator, and her siblings who also serve the students of Caddo
26 Parish; and
27 WHEREAS, Ginger's leadership style, marked by energy, competitiveness,
28 innovation, and genuine care for others, leaves an enduring legacy to the students, faculty,
29 and families at First Baptist Church School in Shreveport and throughout the educational
30 community of Louisiana; and
